The paper focuses on visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework also involves multi-thread techniques, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning-based algorithms, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments involve video datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM).
